                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You should have stopped and hit post before you finished that last paragraph, Saediien.  One of the basic concepts of our government is the notion of a balance of power between the three branches.  If courts couldn't overturn laws there would be no balance of power... the constitution would soon have no meaning because the congress could effectively amend it every time they added a last-minute 'rider' to any bill.
<br />

<br />
I tend to agree with the rest of it... courts are indeed better at procedural stuff and trying criminals.  But if you limit them like that you'll just end up needing a fourth branch to keep Congress in check... that wouldn't be progress.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
