<br />
I think this is exactly why. You protect your rights above everything else - I'm challenging the second ammendment though, and suggesting that limitations be put on this specific right in order to increase freedom within the USA.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I don't have a good answer there. The problem is that there isn't a good solution that doesn't restrict the freedoms and rights of the people.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
