<br />
Only because you've chosen as a nation to allow guns to be part of your rights. I read a good essay this morning which talks about some of the foundational debate on the second ammendment, and read a nice speech by John Handcock talking about the virtues of the Swiss system. Again - guns really do reduce crime and prevent social problems BUT ONLY when coupled with mandatory gun education. I have some more posts to respond to, but since this is getting long I'll stop here and take a lunch break. 
<br />

<br />
Just a quick thank you to everyone for making this thread about the issues at hand, and not about personal attacks and keeping the debate above the table. Guns are the number one concern of mine now that I'm moving to the states, so thanks for bearing with me as I work these issues out in public.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />When I was young I used to pray to God that He would give me a new bicycle. I soon found out that God didn't work that way, so I stole a bike and asked Him to forgive me.
