One of my favorite quotes is from Patrick Henry: "Who gave them the right to say, 'We the People?'"  Furthermore, who gave the Supreme Court the sole and exclusive right to interpret the Constitution?  Answer: the Supreme Court.  I smell a rat.  Judicial review is not by any means necessary.  If courts couldn't overturn laws, then more power would go to the individual states, their courts, and to the people and their elected representatives.  I'm ok with that, because I am uncomfortable with an unaccountable class of Platonic Guardians speaking from on high what Supreme Law of *my* land is.  The constitution already doesn't have any meaning, other than what the Supreme Court says it means.  I really don't see what's so great about that.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=646635" target="_blank" class="postlink">Saediien Iluvatri</a>
